TestCase #4
Summery:Check the edit post
Pre-condition:
1.The user is authorization on the site
2. Click "Create Post" button
3. Enter Title: "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit."
4. Enter Body Content: Nullam iaculis magna ac ex lobortis, quis porttitor urna fringilla.
                       Aliquam odio leo, fermentum sed magna euismod, fringilla semper ipsum.
                       Proin lacus nunc, venenatis volutpat orci ac, maximus sollicitudin ex.
                       Aliquam sit amet nibh eget ex euismod lacinia. Vestibulum semper quam
                       dui, mattis elementum ipsum hendrerit sit amet. Aenean vel ornare massa.
                        Curabitur metus nibh, bibendum non nisl sed, maximus ultrices arcu.
                        Nunc ut erat ultricies, iaculis mi nec, hendrerit nulla. Etiam eros
                        nisl, elementum et eros in, pharetra laoreet odio. Fusce a sollicitudin
                        nunc, sit amet finibus nisl. In hac habitasse platea dictumst.
                        Cras ullamcorper molestie massa, eget consectetur dolor elementum eu.
                         Sed dapibus auctor lectus eu facilisis.
5. Select value "Group Message"
6. Click "Save New Post" button
7. Alert "New post successfully created." displayed
8. Note: This post was written for "Group Message" displayed

Steps fo reproduce:
1. Click "Edit" button
2. Edit title: Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
3. Change select value "Private message"
4. Click "Save Updates" button

Expected result:
1. Alert "Post successfully updated." displayed
2. Click "Back to post permalink" button
3. New title and new status displayed

Post-condition:
1.Delete post
2.Close browser
-------------------------------------------------
TestCase #5
Summery:Check if a chat message has been sent
Pre-condition:
1.The user is authorization on the site

Steps fo reproduce:
1. Click "Chat" button
2. Enter message: "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit."
3. Press "Enter" key

Expected result:
1. The message will be displayed in chat
